SilcsBio Candidate Exercise Instructions
Interactive Visualization Demo for P38 MAP Kinase (PDB: 3FLY) Using SILCS FragMaps
Repository Name Requirement: silcs-fragmaps-demo
1. Overview
As part of the next stage of our interview process, you will build a small interactive demo that visualizes:
● The P38 MAP Kinase protein (PDB 3FLY)
● SILCS FragMaps provided by SilcsBio
● Multiple ligands scored using SILCS‑MC Pose Refinement
● A clear, concise scientific narrative that explains the key interaction features
This exercise is designed to assess your ability to combine scientific understanding, front‑end
development, and communication in a lightweight prototype similar to the current interactive demo on
the silcsbio.com website. You may also refer to a video tutorial for visualizing SILCS FragMaps in SilcsBio
GUI here: https://docs.silcsbio.com/2025/videotutorials.html#
2. Required Repository Setup
Before starting:
1. Create a public GitHub repository named silcs-fragmaps-demo and in configuration add
license type: MIT License.
2. Add aakognole as a collaborator with write access. We will upload input files along with a
README.md file with information on each input file.
3. What You Need to Build
Your interactive demo should include the following elements.
2
A. Overview / Introduction Page
Provide a short, readable explanation covering:
● What P38 MAP Kinase is (biological role)
● The crystal ligand(s) being shown
● What SILCS FragMaps represent
● Why FragMaps help interpret ligand binding
● What the user can do or explore in the demo
This should be concise, 1–2 paragraphs are enough.
B. Interactive Visualization Page (Required)
Use an open‑source web-based 3D visualization library of your choice.
Examples include:
● Mol* (https://molstar.org)
● 3Dmol.js (https://3dmol.csb.pitt.edu)
● LiteMol
● NGL Viewer
Your viewer must support:
● Loading the 3FLY PDB structure
● Showing different bound ligand(s) or the SILCS‑MC refined ligand poses
● Loading and overlaying SILCS FragMaps
● Basic user controls such as:
○ Show/hide individual FragMap surfaces
○ Adjust view (rotate, translate, zoom etc)
○ Adjust iso‑value (slider or preset levels) if possible
Include a simple caption or sidebar describing what the user is seeing.
C. Navigation / Structure
At minimum, your demo should offer:
● Home / Overview
● Interactive Viewer
