4. Technical Requirements
● The website must run entirely client‑side. You may use any free hosting provider, such as: GitHub
Pages, Netlify, Vercel, Render etc. Static hosting is sufficient; no backend services are needed.
● Use only open‑source libraries and tools.
● Include the following in your repo:
○ HTML, CSS, JavaScript or framework code
○ Provided protein PDB and ligand SDF files
○ Provided SILCS FragMaps (.map and .dx format)
○ A clean directory structure (e.g., /assets, /src, etc.)
You may develop using:
● Plain JavaScript
● Vue / React / Svelte
● TypeScript
Framework choice does not affect evaluation.
